commit.message: Add one python / remove all others to push am-extras (#1758) (sync lists) [d0da5a30cd2b439738b28b138339d73c9af9a67c]

Add one "python" / remove all others to push "am-extras" (#1758)

To install multiple versions, use the dedicated third-party database named "python" in "am-extras".

Usage, with extension `.python`
```
am -i python2.7.python python3.5.python [ ... ] python3.14.python
```
or with the flag `--python`
```
am -i --python python2.7 python3.5 [ ... ] python3.14
```

...this change will allow more architectures to choose which variant to install.

---------------------------------------

About the "python" script in AM, using the command
```
am -i python
```
...will instead select only the most recent version (you can still use the `downgrade` option to change versions).
